</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="20997">
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Ampharetidae" genus="Ampharete" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ampharete grubei" order="Terebellida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="grubei">Ampharete grubei</taxonomicName>
had long been considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Ampharetidae" genus="Ampharete" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ampharete acutifrons" order="Terebellida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="acutifrons">Ampharete acutifrons</taxonomicName>
(Grube, 1860) and was reinstated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jirkov, Igor" journalOrPublisher="Yanus-K Press, Moscow" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" title="Polikhety severnogo Ledovitogo Okeana" year="2001">Jirkov (2001)</bibRefCitation>
. Primary literature records from Greece under the name 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Ampharetidae" genus="Ampharete" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ampharete grubei" order="Terebellida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="grubei">Ampharete grubei</taxonomicName>
exist but were subsequently reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Arvanitidis, Christos" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Marine Science" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="73 - 96" title="Polychaete fauna of the Aegean Sea: inventory and new information" volume="66" year="2000">Arvanitidis (2000a)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Simboura, Nomiki" journalOrPublisher="Monographs on Marine Sciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" pagination="1 - 115" title="The Polychaetes (Annelida, Polychaeta) of Greece: Checklist, Distribution and Ecological Characteristics" volume="4" year="2001">Simboura and Nicolaidou (2001)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName class="Polychaeta" family="Ampharetidae" genus="Ampharete" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ampharete acutifrons" order="Terebellida" pageId="0" pageNumber="20997" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="acutifrons">Ampharete acutifrons</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
